WEBVTT

00:17.183 --> 00:19.394
[cell phone ringing]

00:24.107 --> 00:25.108
[sighs]

00:30.905 --> 00:31.906
Nope.

00:32.282 --> 00:35.618
[men] ♪ <i>Hark the herald angels sing</i> ♪

00:35.702 --> 00:38.663
-♪ <i>"Glory to the newborn king"</i> ♪
-[sighs]

00:38.747 --> 00:41.916
♪ <i>Peace on earth and mercy mild</i> ♪

00:43.168 --> 00:45.295
Shut the fuck up! No one cares!

00:45.378 --> 00:49.466
Sophia, did you just tell
the Mission Street-wide Gay Men's Chorus

00:49.549 --> 00:52.552
to shut the fuck up in the season of Yule?

00:52.635 --> 00:54.637
Sorry, Lionel. I didn't see you there.

00:55.138 --> 00:59.184
Yeah. We both know you would've said
the same damn thing if you had.

00:59.267 --> 01:01.311
♪ <i>Hark the herald angels sing</i> ♪

01:01.394 --> 01:04.314
[men continue singing in background]

01:05.023 --> 01:06.316
[sighs]

01:18.745 --> 01:19.746
[sighs]

01:21.581 --> 01:22.582
Mmm.

01:41.935 --> 01:43.144
[belches]

01:46.648 --> 01:48.191
[exhales]

01:52.946 --> 01:55.448
Fuck eBay. Fuck Christmas.

01:55.907 --> 01:59.244
Fuck Annie, fuck Dad,
and fuck ye merry gentlemen!

02:00.912 --> 02:02.163
[sighs]

02:07.210 --> 02:09.420
-[phone beeps]
-[over phone] <i>Sophia, it's Dad.</i>

02:10.463 --> 02:13.758
<i>Just checking to see if you're coming here</i>
<i>for Christmas dinner.</i>

02:13.842 --> 02:17.053
Not if Christ himself took me on muleback.

02:17.887 --> 02:21.349
[Shane] <i>Hey. I know you said</i>
<i>you need some time alone,</i>

02:21.432 --> 02:24.352
<i>but I hope you and Annie</i>
<i>are talking again.</i>

02:24.435 --> 02:26.187
<i>-But if not...</i>
-Oh, we are not.

02:26.271 --> 02:28.982
<i>I wanted to let you know</i>
<i>that I'm here for you.</i>

02:29.357 --> 02:32.110
<i>And I hope you reconsider my offer</i>
<i>to come to Chicago.</i>

02:32.193 --> 02:35.155
<i>You don't even need to bring a present,</i>
<i>like a new bass pedal,</i>

02:35.238 --> 02:38.324
<i>a Gibraltar bass pedal,</i>
<i>a Sonor bass pedal.</i>

02:38.908 --> 02:41.661
<i>Can't stand the thought</i>
<i>of you being alone on Christmas.</i>

02:42.453 --> 02:44.873
<i>I miss you, and... yeah.</i>

02:46.291 --> 02:48.543
<i>Remember, it's cold here. Bring a jacket.</i>

02:54.132 --> 02:55.508
I need a jacket.

02:56.593 --> 03:00.221
[men] ♪ <i>And with true love</i>
<i>And brotherhood </i>♪

03:00.305 --> 03:03.850
♪ <i>Each other now embrace</i> ♪

03:03.933 --> 03:08.771
♪ <i>This holy tide of Christmas</i>
<i>All others</i> ♪

03:08.855 --> 03:10.690
[Le Tigre's "Deceptacon" playing]

03:20.533 --> 03:21.743
What up, Hoss?

03:21.826 --> 03:24.662
A while back, someone at this address
bought a leather jacket from me.

03:24.913 --> 03:26.831
Had a parrot on the collar.

03:26.915 --> 03:29.584
Yeah. It belongs
to the old ball and chain.

03:29.834 --> 03:33.087
Wore it the time we went and visited
that big-ass cave up in Kentucky.

03:33.171 --> 03:34.130
That's great.

03:34.547 --> 03:36.549
See, all of my current misery
can be traced back

03:36.633 --> 03:38.885
to the decision to sell that jacket. So...

03:39.510 --> 03:40.386
I need it.

03:40.470 --> 03:42.513
Hell no.
She paid a lot of money for that.

03:43.598 --> 03:47.352
Well, I can give her two grand cash.

03:48.561 --> 03:49.520
It's yours.

03:51.731 --> 03:52.982
[inhales]

03:53.066 --> 03:54.859
Is she gonna fuck that jacket?

03:54.943 --> 03:57.779
[woman] Mm-hmm.
And then flip it for more money.

03:57.862 --> 04:02.033
-Nope. eBay told me to skedaddle.
-Why'd they go and do that?

04:02.116 --> 04:05.536
'Cause I was hornswoggled
by a no-good snake in the grass.

04:05.620 --> 04:07.538
I don't know why I'm talking like this.

04:07.622 --> 04:09.791
I know what we do to snakes
down here in Texas.

04:09.874 --> 04:12.543
-Hm?
-Cut their heads off, suck out the meat.

04:15.296 --> 04:16.464
Merry Christmas.

04:17.006 --> 04:19.926
<i>♪ Who took the Bomp</i>
<i>From the Bompalompalomp? ♪</i>

04:20.009 --> 04:22.929
<i>♪ Who took the Ram</i>
<i>From the Rama Lama Ding Dong? ♪</i>

04:23.012 --> 04:26.057
<i>♪ Who took the Bomp</i>
<i>From the Bompalompalomp? ♪</i>

04:26.140 --> 04:28.059
<i>♪ Who took the Ram</i>
<i>From the Rama Lama... ♪</i>

04:28.142 --> 04:29.978
[doorbell rings]

04:30.645 --> 04:31.980
♪ <i>See you later</i> ♪

04:33.815 --> 04:35.066
♪ <i>See you later</i> ♪

04:36.693 --> 04:39.028
Sophia, what a surprise.

04:39.320 --> 04:41.823
Please, come in.
I'm just finishing up a Hungry-Man.

04:41.906 --> 04:44.867
Cut the fake hospitality.
I know it was you.

04:45.868 --> 04:48.454
It wasn't personal. It's just business.

04:48.830 --> 04:51.291
You of all people
can surely understand that.

04:51.374 --> 04:53.626
Don't you hoist me on my own petard.

04:53.710 --> 04:56.337
eBay kicked you off, Sophia. I did not.

04:56.421 --> 04:59.382
So, as far as I'm concerned,
we're finished here.

04:59.465 --> 05:01.759
Unless you would like half
of my Salisbury steak.

05:01.843 --> 05:03.720
Because the portion is too big for me.

05:04.304 --> 05:06.222
You best understand one thing.

05:06.681 --> 05:09.392
For the rest of your life,
I'm gonna be out there

05:09.475 --> 05:11.102
waiting for my moment.

05:11.686 --> 05:15.315
You'll never know when
or how I'm gonna strike.

05:15.398 --> 05:18.109
You best understand one thing.

05:18.192 --> 05:19.444
I will be ready--

05:21.654 --> 05:25.158
You... bopped me on the... ear.

05:25.241 --> 05:26.743
Snakes don't have ears.

05:29.203 --> 05:32.457
I am giving you three seconds to leave.

05:32.707 --> 05:35.251
Not until I suck the meat out of your ass.

05:35.335 --> 05:38.379
That's a straight-up Nasty Gal threat
with a Texas twist.

05:38.463 --> 05:39.714
-Time's up!
-Oh!

05:40.423 --> 05:42.216
[gasping]

05:42.300 --> 05:45.386
Such a... strong... grip.

05:45.470 --> 05:48.598
You... are a garbage person.

05:49.849 --> 05:53.728
No wonder your mother left.
I'd have left you, too.

06:06.616 --> 06:09.619
♪ <i>Have yourself a merry little Christmas</i> ♪

06:09.702 --> 06:12.121
[inaudible dialogue]

06:13.790 --> 06:18.377
<i>♪ Let your heart be light ♪</i>

06:20.296 --> 06:22.882
♪ <i>From now on</i> ♪

06:22.965 --> 06:29.180
<i>♪ Our troubles will be out of sight ♪</i>

06:31.140 --> 06:33.935
[man on PA] <i>Attention, arriving passengers</i>
<i>with ground transportation</i>

06:34.018 --> 06:35.853
<i>to Crystal Bay or Incline Village,</i>

06:36.437 --> 06:39.941
<i>please see the Customer Service kiosk</i>
<i>located in the High Mountain Marketplace</i>

06:40.024 --> 06:41.984
-<i>to confirm weather conditions.</i>
-Thank you.

06:42.110 --> 06:45.196
-I need to change my flight.
-How will Santa know where to find you?

06:45.780 --> 06:48.491
He can look up the next time
he's eating out my ass.

06:50.576 --> 06:51.452
Where you headed?

06:53.037 --> 06:55.665
[instrumental "Deck the Halls" playing]

07:24.569 --> 07:25.570
[man] Mr. Cratchit,

07:25.945 --> 07:28.781
you will be working right here with me.

07:29.449 --> 07:30.700
As you wish, sir.

07:34.537 --> 07:35.997
I miss Father.

07:36.998 --> 07:41.169
I so wish we could spend
Christmas together as a family.

07:41.419 --> 07:42.670
Me, too, Tiny Tim.

07:43.171 --> 07:45.006
Your father is a good man.

07:45.381 --> 07:49.343
But, sadly, he works for a dastardly one.

07:49.427 --> 07:53.264
Is there anything that can thaw
his frozen heart?

07:53.556 --> 07:54.682
[coughing]

07:54.765 --> 07:57.185
I mean, it's not like he's Dick Cheney.

07:57.268 --> 07:59.604
[laughter]

08:05.693 --> 08:07.361
[gagging]

08:21.375 --> 08:22.919
[yelling]

08:23.503 --> 08:24.754
Bah...

08:25.129 --> 08:26.339
[audience laughs]

08:26.422 --> 08:27.840
Humbug.

08:30.301 --> 08:34.555
Zounds! Scrooge has met his end most foul.

08:34.639 --> 08:36.265
Who could the killer be?

08:36.516 --> 08:41.062
Was it Rosemary Shockey,
who turned 70 today?

08:44.899 --> 08:46.400
[all] ♪ <i>Some will come clean</i> ♪

08:46.484 --> 08:48.486
♪ <i>All I do</i> ♪

08:48.569 --> 08:51.948
♪ <i>Is come</i> ♪

08:52.031 --> 08:57.578
♪ <i>Clean</i> ♪

09:16.722 --> 09:18.516
Excuse me, Tiny Tim?

09:19.058 --> 09:21.060
I'm a real person, you know.
I have a name.

09:21.143 --> 09:22.562
Sorry. What is it?

09:23.104 --> 09:25.064
-People call me Topper.
-Ah.

09:26.274 --> 09:27.733
Uh, you want some tabacky?

09:29.026 --> 09:31.779
-No, thanks.
-Okay. Well, you can't be back here, then.

09:32.363 --> 09:34.448
Actually, I'm looking
for Kathleen Downing.

09:34.532 --> 09:36.200
Oh, sure.

09:36.284 --> 09:38.661
You know her name. She's in there.

09:43.708 --> 09:44.750
[Kathleen] Sophia?

09:54.093 --> 09:55.052
Hi, Mom.

09:56.095 --> 09:57.430
It is you.

10:00.391 --> 10:02.226
Oh, my God.

10:03.978 --> 10:05.104
Look at you.

10:06.063 --> 10:06.939
Yeah.

10:08.941 --> 10:10.610
You're beautiful.

10:13.904 --> 10:15.573
Are you here to yell at me?

10:16.949 --> 10:19.785
-No. I'm--
-I can't get over how good you look.

10:19.869 --> 10:21.287
You're so grown up.

10:21.829 --> 10:23.998
Pulling off bangs,
you still got that dimple,

10:24.081 --> 10:25.833
and this jacket, so punk.

10:25.916 --> 10:26.792
Yeah.

10:26.876 --> 10:30.171
I love a jacket that says,
"Get the fuck out of my way, world."

10:31.088 --> 10:32.340
Wow.

10:34.216 --> 10:35.635
So much to take in.

10:38.971 --> 10:42.475
I know... I should have been
more in touch.

10:43.017 --> 10:47.355
But between the moves,
and that hospital stay for my migraines,

10:47.438 --> 10:48.898
and everything with Katrina...

10:48.981 --> 10:50.066
It's okay, Mom.

10:50.733 --> 10:52.109
Wow.

10:53.486 --> 10:55.071
This is a heavy moment for me.

10:55.154 --> 10:56.364
[chuckles]

10:56.447 --> 10:57.782
A cocktail will help.

11:00.201 --> 11:01.994
Cast party started 20 minutes ago.

11:02.078 --> 11:04.246
If we don't leave now,
they'll drink the place dry.

11:04.330 --> 11:05.706
[both chuckle]

11:05.790 --> 11:07.041
You think I'm kidding.

11:07.625 --> 11:08.959
I work pretty consistently.

11:09.043 --> 11:12.171
I mean, it's not Broadway or anything,
but I love it.

11:12.797 --> 11:17.426
I'm just waiting for that one lead role
to take my career to the next level.

11:18.511 --> 11:21.514
-So, Chuck, the guy that played Scrooge,
-Uh-huh.

11:21.597 --> 11:24.517
he's the theater's artistic director.
He keeps dropping hints

11:24.600 --> 11:28.270
that I could be Anna in <i>The King and I</i>
after New Year's.

11:28.354 --> 11:31.357
Mmm. I'm sure you'll get it.
You're really talented.

11:31.899 --> 11:34.568
Well, it doesn't matter
how talented you are.

11:35.444 --> 11:39.699
[sighs] The harsh reality is
moms don't land lead roles.

11:39.990 --> 11:42.493
Reese Witherspoon's a mom,
and she did all right.

11:43.661 --> 11:45.121
Her last movie sucked.

11:47.206 --> 11:48.499
Won her an Oscar.

11:50.876 --> 11:53.045
Here's the thing. Chuck,

11:53.129 --> 11:56.090
he thinks I'm in my mid-30s
'cause I told him I'm in my mid-30s.

11:56.173 --> 11:58.217
So, if I introduce him
to my grown daughter--

11:58.300 --> 12:00.010
Say no more. I'll follow your lead.

12:01.929 --> 12:04.557
By the way, Gary,
please come to the vocal warm-ups.

12:04.640 --> 12:05.891
Say "pestilence."

12:05.975 --> 12:07.351
-Pestilence.
-Pestilence.

12:07.435 --> 12:09.228
-Pestilence.
-[Kathleen] I'm here, gentlemen.

12:09.311 --> 12:10.980
Put your dicks away.

12:11.063 --> 12:12.731
I'll do no such thing.

12:13.899 --> 12:16.777
Chuck, your death scene seems
to be getting longer

12:16.861 --> 12:19.071
and more moving every night.
The crowd loved it.

12:19.280 --> 12:22.158
Oh, it's... still not there yet.

12:22.241 --> 12:24.910
But I was really living in the harmony
of our duet.

12:24.994 --> 12:26.454
Oh, I felt it, too.

12:26.954 --> 12:28.622
Symbiosis. And who is this?

12:29.206 --> 12:31.667
Oh, this is Colette. She's my manicurist.

12:32.376 --> 12:34.920
Yep. I do nails.

12:35.004 --> 12:37.798
-Doing nails? How's that going for you?
-Mm-hmm.

12:37.882 --> 12:38.716
Good.

12:40.468 --> 12:45.514
Uh, in many ways, a woman's strength
is defined by her nails.

12:45.973 --> 12:47.683
That's why she should keep them long.

12:47.766 --> 12:51.312
With bold, assertive colors
to alert others to her presence.

12:51.395 --> 12:54.356
I mean, we're all primal beings,
and these are our claws.

12:54.440 --> 12:56.692
What do you think the first cave paintings
were made from?

12:56.775 --> 12:58.110
The first clay tablets?

12:58.194 --> 13:00.946
Art, literature, math, civilization.

13:01.238 --> 13:03.324
It all comes from the nails.

13:05.993 --> 13:07.786
That is fucking great.

13:08.412 --> 13:10.664
[chuckles] I'm gonna get us a pitcher.

13:11.207 --> 13:12.625
Yeah, I'll get us a table.

13:13.834 --> 13:15.753
I loved when you broke.

13:15.836 --> 13:18.881
Oh, the audience adores it.
I can teach you.

13:19.507 --> 13:22.384
Tiny Tim coming in from the back,
that was my idea.

13:22.468 --> 13:25.930
Yeah, it's sneakier that way.
You know, you gotta take the audience

13:26.180 --> 13:27.223
on a ride.

13:27.306 --> 13:29.850
Well, it also gives
that cop guy a place to run.

13:29.934 --> 13:32.353
The stage is way too small
for a whole chase.

13:32.436 --> 13:34.438
You don't know what you're talking about.
Thing is--

13:34.522 --> 13:36.357
-[Kathleen] Hey, Topper.
-Yeah?

13:36.440 --> 13:39.443
I overheard someone back there
saying your limp was inauthentic.

13:40.152 --> 13:42.655
Somebody back there is full of shit.

13:43.447 --> 13:47.826
Inauthentic. I worked for two weeks
with a war veteran on that limp.

13:47.910 --> 13:52.081
Inauthentic. Hey! Inauth--
Does this look inauthentic to you?

13:52.540 --> 13:53.874
Hey, you.

13:54.833 --> 13:57.044
That idiot drives me crazy.

13:57.545 --> 13:58.837
So self-absorbed.

13:58.921 --> 14:01.048
-So, how'd it go with Chuck?
-Good, I think.

14:01.632 --> 14:04.760
I asked about the part, he said he was
this close to making a decision.

14:04.843 --> 14:08.264
All right, Kathleen! Taking control.

14:08.347 --> 14:09.932
Yeah.

14:10.224 --> 14:12.101
Now, a woman my age would never high five.

14:12.184 --> 14:14.144
-But a woman in her 30s...
-Mm-hmm.

14:14.770 --> 14:16.397
He seems like an okay guy.

14:16.480 --> 14:19.149
Chuck? God, no, he's disgusting.

14:19.233 --> 14:21.777
He claims to have slept with
over a thousand women.

14:21.861 --> 14:22.695
That guy?

14:22.778 --> 14:25.155
Did not take him long
to tell me that either.

14:25.239 --> 14:26.282
Who's that lady?

14:27.825 --> 14:29.785
Oh, that's Nikki.

14:30.953 --> 14:32.121
She's new to the company.

14:32.204 --> 14:34.540
She's sweet,
but she's way heavier than she looks.

14:35.124 --> 14:37.585
Are you sure blondie's not gunning
for that lead part?

14:37.668 --> 14:39.712
She's really chatting him up over there.

14:40.212 --> 14:44.508
[Kathleen] Well, Chuck's the king.
It means he can hit on whoever he wants.

14:44.592 --> 14:46.719
The rules of the stage.

14:47.136 --> 14:50.806
Mmm. That doesn't sound real.
To hell with the rules.

14:50.890 --> 14:52.099
Go and stop that shit.

14:52.182 --> 14:54.226
You know what? You're right.

14:55.436 --> 14:56.645
To hell with the rules.

14:56.729 --> 14:59.148
[rock music playing over speakers]

15:02.401 --> 15:04.403
[inaudible dialogue]

15:09.533 --> 15:12.369
I think I'm gonna get this part.
I'm gonna be Anna.

15:12.453 --> 15:13.996
I'm gonna be the "I."

15:14.079 --> 15:17.041
Nice. You can act circles
around that Nikki.

15:17.708 --> 15:21.003
Right? Okay, wait here.
I gotta go fuck Chuck in the bathroom.

15:21.086 --> 15:24.298
-What? No. That's not what I meant.
-It's gonna work.

15:24.381 --> 15:26.383
I don't want to brag, but I'm pretty good.

15:27.426 --> 15:28.844
-But--
-I've had way worse.

15:28.928 --> 15:32.139
I did a show once with that creepy
little guy from <i>Ally McBeal.</i>

15:34.016 --> 15:35.184
[sighs]

15:35.267 --> 15:37.645
All I know is,
no one else is getting that part.

15:40.189 --> 15:43.108
Couldn't find the guy. Coward.

15:43.192 --> 15:47.196
So, why don't you tell me your life story?

15:49.406 --> 15:51.116
Are you a boy or a girl?

15:52.076 --> 15:53.369
Let's find out.

15:57.831 --> 16:00.084
-You finished?
-Well, I didn't, but Chuck did.

16:02.211 --> 16:03.212
Let's go.

16:06.840 --> 16:08.926
I was with this one company in Des Moines.

16:09.009 --> 16:12.054
Some crazy, wild people in that theater.

16:12.137 --> 16:16.016
One night... a bottle of 100-proof tequila

16:16.100 --> 16:18.018
was poured on the stage

16:18.102 --> 16:21.855
-and the whole damn thing lit on fire.
-[chuckles]

16:21.939 --> 16:25.526
George Wendt lost an eyebrow.
Do you know who he is?

16:26.610 --> 16:28.237
He's the married one on <i>Cheers</i>.

16:28.696 --> 16:30.990
Seems fun. Why'd you leave?

16:31.407 --> 16:35.035
Well, they canceled the show
until the stage could be rebuilt.

16:35.536 --> 16:38.247
I didn't want to wait around
until next season.

16:38.330 --> 16:40.249
So, I moved on.

16:40.624 --> 16:43.085
-[Sophia] You've been all over.
-Yeah.

16:43.585 --> 16:44.878
Wait, stop.

16:46.755 --> 16:49.258
Tomorrow is Christmas,
and I don't have a tree.

16:50.426 --> 16:51.552
You want to steal one?

16:53.429 --> 16:55.222
Hell, yeah.

16:55.305 --> 16:57.933
[soul music playing]

16:59.852 --> 17:02.062
[both laughing]

17:04.231 --> 17:05.983
[Kathleen] It's a victimless crime, right?

17:06.066 --> 17:10.279
Yeah. Trees grow out of the ground.
So, how can you really own one to sell?

17:10.362 --> 17:11.864
You know, in 24 hours,

17:11.947 --> 17:15.284
these trees will just be
basically trash on the side of the road.

17:15.659 --> 17:17.411
-[Sophia] Ow!
-Okay. Okay.

17:18.412 --> 17:21.498
[grunts] We have no upper-body strength.

17:22.082 --> 17:23.292
Help us, Jesus.

17:23.876 --> 17:27.421
Help us steal. Silent night. [screams]

17:27.504 --> 17:28.964
Oh, it's stuck. It's stuck.

17:29.465 --> 17:31.091
[laughing]

17:32.134 --> 17:32.968
Yes!

17:35.012 --> 17:39.099
It doesn't really matter, because,
you know, Nasty Gal no longer exists.

17:39.183 --> 17:41.477
But she still doesn't wanna talk to me.

17:42.061 --> 17:43.729
You don't need her.

17:44.396 --> 17:46.398
You don't need anyone.

17:46.482 --> 17:49.610
Well, I kind of need, like,
the barista at Starbucks.

17:49.693 --> 17:52.446
'Cause, what, am I gonna,
like, hit a bunch of buttons,

17:52.529 --> 17:54.114
and then foam appears?

17:54.198 --> 17:56.742
-[laughs]
-Ta-da!

17:57.117 --> 18:00.621
Is it an ornament,
or a tangle of Satan's pubes?

18:00.704 --> 18:02.122
[chuckles]

18:03.207 --> 18:06.710
Gosh, you're so cool and fun.

18:07.878 --> 18:08.879
[groans]

18:10.672 --> 18:13.592
Why didn't I see that when you were 12?

18:16.553 --> 18:18.972
Well, we're out of wine.

18:19.973 --> 18:21.391
All we have is this.

18:21.475 --> 18:25.354
And there's not enough for the both of us,
so I'm just gonna take it.

18:26.980 --> 18:27.815
Mom.

18:28.482 --> 18:29.650
Mm?

18:31.735 --> 18:32.820
Why did you leave?

18:36.156 --> 18:37.699
[sighing] Oh, honey.

18:38.951 --> 18:39.868
Well...

18:44.123 --> 18:46.416
I know it's hard to understand, but I...

18:49.002 --> 18:51.547
I just had to get out of there.

18:53.215 --> 18:56.802
So, you don't think that I'm...
a garbage person?

18:56.885 --> 18:58.512
No, no.

18:58.595 --> 18:59.972
No, no, no.

19:01.557 --> 19:05.477
It had nothing to do with you.
I mean, it wasn't my dream to be a mother.

19:05.561 --> 19:07.771
But your father was...

19:08.480 --> 19:11.066
We... were doing so well.

19:11.150 --> 19:15.237
And then... suddenly,
he just stopped believing in me.

19:15.779 --> 19:16.738
Why?

19:16.989 --> 19:19.032
It's what he does.

19:20.367 --> 19:21.994
He crushes dreams.

19:23.579 --> 19:24.454
Yeah.

19:24.955 --> 19:27.166
There are a lot of things
I wasn't around to teach you.

19:27.249 --> 19:29.334
But here's something that I can:

19:30.544 --> 19:36.049
in life, the only one
who can make you happy is you.

19:37.593 --> 19:40.762
The great big lie
is that we need other people.

19:42.472 --> 19:45.017
But... [clears throat] No.

19:46.685 --> 19:47.895
The truth is...

19:51.064 --> 19:53.108
we all die alone.

19:54.568 --> 19:55.402
Totally.

19:59.323 --> 20:01.283
I really am my mother's daughter.

20:03.076 --> 20:07.456
You are your mother's manicurist.

20:08.123 --> 20:10.667
[both laughing]

20:14.171 --> 20:16.423
Well, I guess I...

20:17.132 --> 20:19.968
I'd better...
I'd better get to bed if I'm going to get

20:20.052 --> 20:21.845
my beauty sleep before the matinee.

20:22.429 --> 20:23.764
Make yourself at home.

20:25.557 --> 20:29.394
Hey. Why don't you stay a little longer?

20:29.478 --> 20:33.815
Like through the new year,
or as long as you want?

20:34.983 --> 20:38.362
Sure. Yeah.

20:56.421 --> 20:58.423
[all singing scales]

21:03.845 --> 21:04.846
Fun night, huh?

21:04.930 --> 21:06.431
Yeah, pretty fun.

21:06.515 --> 21:09.601
There'll be lots of nights like that
to come once you're my king.

21:10.185 --> 21:11.395
What do you mean?

21:11.979 --> 21:14.022
Anna does whatever her king asks.

21:14.731 --> 21:16.900
And I mean whatever.

21:17.901 --> 21:21.238
Oh, Kathleen, I'm sorry,
but Anna's going to someone else.

21:22.948 --> 21:26.159
-Wait. What was last night about?
-Last night?

21:26.243 --> 21:29.371
That was just two actors releasing
some pent-up energy after a show.

21:30.956 --> 21:33.750
You're joking right now, right?
This is a fucking joke.

21:33.834 --> 21:36.169
No. And even if I were,
it wouldn't change the fact

21:36.253 --> 21:38.964
that you are just too old
to play the role.

21:39.548 --> 21:42.718
I mean, I'm sorry, but Anna can't be 50.

21:44.261 --> 21:46.638
This is bullshit, and you know it, Chuck.

21:46.722 --> 21:48.515
I deserve that part.

21:51.435 --> 21:54.896
Well, if it's not me,
then who did get it?

21:56.648 --> 21:58.400
Tell me. Who got the part?

21:59.318 --> 22:01.737
As is customary,
I was going to make a formal announcement.

22:01.820 --> 22:04.990
But since you must know,
my lords, ladies, and gentlemen,

22:05.073 --> 22:07.743
the part of Anna in <i>The King and I</i>
goes to Nikki.

22:08.285 --> 22:09.536
Congratulations, Nikki.

22:09.911 --> 22:11.121
[laughing] Oh, shit.

22:13.582 --> 22:15.208
What's so funny, Topper?

22:15.834 --> 22:17.169
-Nothing.
-[Kathleen] Hm?

22:17.252 --> 22:19.504
'Cause the only thing
that I think is funny

22:19.588 --> 22:23.759
is your pathetic British accent.
It's almost as bad as Keith's résumé.

22:23.842 --> 22:26.219
-What the fuck did I do to you?
-It's not just you.

22:26.303 --> 22:28.972
It's this whole shitty,
amateurish production.

22:29.056 --> 22:30.974
-Jesus, Kathleen. Let's go outside--
-No!

22:31.058 --> 22:33.185
You're gonna shut up and listen to me.

22:33.268 --> 22:36.980
You wouldn't know a good actor
if she shit down your mouth.

22:37.064 --> 22:39.900
This entire theater lacks artistic merit.

22:39.983 --> 22:43.987
And you... You are a lousy lay.

22:44.696 --> 22:46.990
-Are you done?
-Oh, yeah, I'm done.

22:47.532 --> 22:50.994
-I'm out of here forever.
-[Chuck] Really? Where are you gonna go?

22:51.078 --> 22:53.747
-I'll go back to Des Moines.
-Des Moines, that's rich.

22:53.830 --> 22:56.583
You think Bobby's gonna take you back
after what you pulled?

22:56.666 --> 22:59.419
His fire insurance premiums
have doubled thanks to you.

22:59.503 --> 23:01.004
[Kathleen] I'll go back to Carbondale.

23:01.088 --> 23:03.632
Have fun.
Say hi to my picture on the wall.

23:05.926 --> 23:07.177
Fuck you, Topper.

23:07.260 --> 23:10.013
-Hey, hey, hey.
-Fuck all of you!

23:11.223 --> 23:13.183
Fuck this place and fuck everything!

23:14.434 --> 23:16.228
You can all kiss my ass.

23:19.272 --> 23:20.107
We're leaving.

23:22.943 --> 23:25.153
This is perfect.
It's Christmas, won't be any traffic.

23:25.237 --> 23:28.615
We'll just blow out of here
and not even look back.

23:29.199 --> 23:30.367
Blow out of here where?

23:30.951 --> 23:33.412
Oh, I don't know.
Somewhere. I'll figure it out.

23:34.538 --> 23:37.040
Hawaii. Oh, let's go there.

23:37.290 --> 23:39.543
We'll just lie on the beach
and eat pineapple

23:39.626 --> 23:42.379
-and be alone together.
-[horn honking]

23:50.137 --> 23:51.763
You're not coming with me, are you?

23:53.098 --> 23:54.015
No.

23:56.351 --> 23:58.979
Fine. Okay.

24:15.453 --> 24:16.580
Merry Christmas.

24:17.539 --> 24:18.582
I couldn't.

24:19.416 --> 24:20.250
Take it.

24:21.042 --> 24:23.753
For the next time you need
to tell the world to fuck off.

24:32.929 --> 24:33.889
Bye, Mom.

24:48.570 --> 24:52.657
♪ <i>Hark the herald angels sing</i> ♪

24:52.741 --> 24:56.786
♪ <i>"Glory to the newborn king"</i> ♪

24:56.870 --> 25:01.041
♪ <i>Peace on earth, and mercy mild</i> ♪

25:01.124 --> 25:05.045
<i>♪ God and sinners reconciled ♪</i>

25:05.128 --> 25:07.672
Good timing. I don't know what
the rest of the words are.

25:07.756 --> 25:09.090
I have nothing to say to you.

25:09.174 --> 25:11.092
I have one thing to say to you.

25:13.803 --> 25:17.224
I'm sorry. And thank you.

25:18.099 --> 25:19.267
That's two things.

25:20.143 --> 25:21.770
Thank you? For what?

25:21.853 --> 25:25.357
Getting me kicked off eBay
was the best gift you could have given me.

25:25.690 --> 25:29.361
'Cause now I'm gonna do things right.
I'm done being a garbage person.

25:31.196 --> 25:33.073
You're never getting back on eBay.

25:33.406 --> 25:36.910
It's not me,
but once you lose eBay's trust,

25:37.244 --> 25:38.578
it holds a grudge.

25:38.662 --> 25:41.498
It's okay. I'll start my own site.

25:41.748 --> 25:45.710
Maybe it'll work, maybe it won't.
But it'll be mine.

25:48.213 --> 25:49.256
Wait.

25:50.090 --> 25:51.132
You're welcome.

25:52.717 --> 25:53.677
Wait.

25:54.469 --> 25:55.679
May I sing with you?

25:56.263 --> 25:57.514
Oh, I have a flight to catch--

25:57.597 --> 26:00.058
<i>♪ Joy to the world ♪</i>

26:00.141 --> 26:03.144
<i>♪ The Lord has come ♪</i>

26:06.231 --> 26:07.732
<i>♪ Let earth ♪</i>

26:07.816 --> 26:09.734
[mumbles]

